Heat 1 teaspoon oil in large nonstick skillet over medium high heat. Cook ham steaks in skillet for 3 to 4 minutes turning once. Remove steaks to serving platter and cover to keep warm. Add remaining tablespoon of oil to pan. Cook peppers and onion blend and pineapple in oil for 4 to 5 minutes or until onion is tender. Stir in teriyaki marinade and red pepper flakes and heat briefly until bubbly. Spoon pineapple mixture over ham. Sprinkle chopped green onion over all.